rComments: passionate about econs, will help you outside of class for further understanding
Both courses were mathy and a little abstract but his tests are fair, he tries to teach material that isn't in the textbook and he seems to always be happy to help. Great prof.
One of the best professors I've ever had. Go to class, do the work - you will do well.

This prof has no organization nor passion. He has no lecture notes that aid student to understand the materials. He scribbles on the board and go on and on about a bunch of symbols and tell you this is the reality of life. He will make you wanna murder yourself

I agree with the person below him. He tried to intimidate you with all the math symbols but it is easier than what it seems. He is very helpful in his office hours and really nice when you are a hard working student.

he's a really good prof i really enjoyed having him. if you do not know a lot about math and stats you might find his courses hard at the beginning but then you get used to him. he makes everything he does in class seem like its impossible to do it on  your own, but its way easier than what everybody thinks
he teaches well, exams are very easy.
no website, useless lectures, with TAs late for tests

I think that ECO206 with Gagnon was fairly easy, considering he reuses many questions from past tests (which are all posted on ERES), so none of the midterms were surprising in anyway. I recommend learning to take notes as opposed to blindly copying down what is written the board. Class material is more relevant than the text.

Do not take any courses with this Professor. He is one of the most vicious and tormented souls, who has no life and takes refuge in slowly torturing his students. The challenges you will face in his class are unfair because the instruction is much worse than Professors, who give harder exams. So, Gagnon is a deadly Professor. Watch out!

Took 3 courses w/ him, 208/328/325, I got A in all 3, so you can trust me. He try to make the lecture incomprehensible and make you think it's too hard, but it's good, bad students fail terribly (drop class avg). His stuff might look confusing but it's really(!) easy if you actually try a bit. Proofs are shown in class, but not required to get 85+.

This guy doesn't use a website, doesn't have slides, teaches directly off the blackboard with his chicken scratch freehand, and doesn't even have the decency to stand up when he's talking. I'm serious. This guy sits down while he lectures. If you don't sit in the first three rows, you cannot see him.
I appreciate him a LOT right now, when I'm taking all these 300-level ECO courses. He is great and probably the most knowledgeable and intellingent prof in the Economics Department

He is knowledgeable and theoretical. It is not easy to follow him all the time, not because of his clarity, but for the nature of the materials. One needs maths and stats thinking to understand some concepts in the models. He doesn't seem approachable when one first meets him, but in fact he is a very nice person. You will learn some serious econs.

Lots of people hate this guy, but I found him the best on the 200 level. Extremely knowledgeable and intelligent, no surprises on tests. Sometimes he goes a bit too fast and all of a sudden gives all those math theories, but at least you learn something from his classes.
His notes and graphs are extremely messy, not to mention that he doesn't put down much of what he says on the board....it's often hard to follow his verbal explainations.
He is very good. Knows his material and tries to help the students towards understaning it.
This prof is erudite in stats and macroeconomic modelling. Explains very clearly. Tests are fair. Seems unapproachable on the surface, but friendly.
Worst prof. i ever met! He doesn't care about teaching at all. The tests and final are disasters!! Avoid him at any cost!!!
Look at past paper before you write your midterms. Lots of the questions are from past papers! Beside the fact that he's very boring and yawn every 5s, he's a very good prof
Terrible teaching and unreadable handwriting. Worst prof. I have ever met in my life!!! So scared about my final. I am sure he will bring a disaster to our GPA!!!
He's a complete ****, but I don't think he's a bad professor. He tests what he teaches. I can't ask for anything more than that.
He's a bad teacher but his class is a lot easier than Yang's...

Say all you want about the guy, I like him. He purposely teaches in such a way that people who aren't paying attention or don't study properly will do badly. This is a good thing because he doesn't need to make the tests all that hard if he wants to get a 65% average. If you do pay attention, you'll pass with flying colors. Nice guy too.
He's not THAT bad, but yeah...it can get confusing and it seems like he's dieing out there. At least we get Jump next term, who is supposedly better.
Unhelpful notes. Unclear solutions. Does no examples in class. Uses ambiguous words to explain straightforward concepts.
just terrible :) textbook has nothing to do with what he is teaching at class. unreadable handwriting. cant explain anything.
Very hard, not the most helpful prof either.
unhelpful, when I emailed him, he did not want to assist me, he just wants me to refer to the TA.
initaally i thought he was gonna pass out from an asthma attack. i wish that was the case.
he knows whats hes talking about but its really difficult to follow what hes saying,,way too fast and its hard to keep up with him.

I just finished the final, damn hard, noting to do with what's taught in class. WTF!!!  terrible prof.  Avoid him like plague!

Perhaps a good researcher,but absolutely a terrible teacher. Explains easy concepts in a way that is hard to understand, explains hard concepts in a way that is impossible to understand. Poor handwritting. No enthusiasm at all. The worst prof ever.
i hate this guy, why UT even hire ppl like this.
sighs every minutes or so, goes way to fast, sometimes it seems like he's talking to himself. avoid him if possible.
WORST PROF EVER, i am taking his 208 class right now, holy god, every 2 seconds he sighs, i am sure he doesn't wanna teach, what a joke.
Avoid taking his course. But seems he is the only choice. Poor us.
Too fast, teaches beyond the course requirement, no enthusiasm for teaching, very boring. He makes it obvious he doesn't want to be in class.
very boring, teaches way too fast

Undoubtedly, he is very smart. However, he is a poor presenter and not strong at teaching others. The strong impression is that he teaches only because it is a requirement in order for him to continue his research.
a serious guy!!
oh, my god!boring!

It just wasn't good to sit in his class. sighs ALOT. extends way beyond textbook. Tests are ok, similar to notes and questions. He also taught @ Ryerson University, look at ratings there too. Have fun my fellow second year U of T students.
